00:09:12,936 --> 00:09:14,102
- I never should've quit,

234
00:09:14,137 --> 00:09:17,138
because even though
I really, really like to win,

235
00:09:17,174 --> 00:09:19,941
I know now that
it's okay to lose.

236
00:09:19,977 --> 00:09:22,110
I sang a song about it
and everything!

237
00:09:22,145 --> 00:09:23,945
- Oh, singing.
Okay.

238
00:09:23,981 --> 00:09:25,180
See, why didn't we
think of that?

239
00:09:25,215 --> 00:09:26,948
- I don't know, Piggy.

240
00:09:26,984 --> 00:09:29,117
You just get sort of mad
when you lose.

241
00:09:29,152 --> 00:09:31,219
   <i> - A dramatic turn of events!</i>

242
00:09:31,255 --> 00:09:33,088
- If you just give me
another chance,

243
00:09:33,123 --> 00:09:35,257
you'll see I won't
do that anymore.

244
00:09:35,292 --> 00:09:37,225
- Well, we do need
one more person

245
00:09:37,261 --> 00:09:38,960
to play the final game.

246
00:09:38,996 --> 00:09:40,929
 <i> - Will they give her a chance?</i>

247
00:09:40,964 --> 00:09:43,031
   - Aw, give the pig a chance.
             - Yeah!

248
00:09:43,066 --> 00:09:44,266
                - Well, what are
                we waiting for?

249
00:09:44,301 --> 00:09:47,035
           Let's race!
           [all cheer]

250
00:09:47,070 --> 00:09:48,903
             - Yay!

251
00:09:48,939 --> 00:09:50,905
   The Sport-A-Thon is back on
      with the final event.

252
00:09:50,941 --> 00:09:52,974
      <i> Who will make it down</i>
     <i> the bobsled track first?</i>

253
00:09:53,010 --> 00:09:56,077
   <i> Will it be Piggy and Summer</i>
       <i> or Animal and Gonzo?</i>

254
00:09:56,113 --> 00:09:59,014
- Either way, it's all downhill
from here, Kermit.

255
00:09:59,049 --> 00:10:01,082
Eh? Wocka wocka!

256
00:10:01,118 --> 00:10:03,151
        [crickets chirp]

257
00:10:03,186 --> 00:10:07,122
[clears throat]
Bobsledders, are you ready?

258
00:10:07,157 --> 00:10:08,957
                      [together]
                          Ready!

259
00:10:08,992 --> 00:10:10,258
- Good luck, you guys.

260
00:10:10,294 --> 00:10:12,227
                       - Thanks.
                        You too.

261
00:10:12,262 --> 00:10:15,063
- On your mark...
get set...

262
00:10:15,098 --> 00:10:16,097
               go!
        [air horn sounds]

263
00:10:16,133 --> 00:10:17,198
             - Whoo-hoo-hoo-hoo!

264
00:10:17,234 --> 00:10:19,134
       <i> - And they're off!</i>

265
00:10:19,169 --> 00:10:21,102
   <i> The racers fly down the drop</i>
     <i> and into the first turn.</i>

266
00:10:21,138 --> 00:10:23,038
      <i> It's Gonzo and Animal</i>
           <i> in the lead.</i>

267
00:10:23,073 --> 00:10:26,041
         [all laughing]

268
00:10:26,076 --> 00:10:27,242
    <i> It's still anyone's race</i>

269
00:10:27,277 --> 00:10:28,977
          <i> as they enter</i>
        <i> the swervy-swerve.</i>

270
00:10:29,012 --> 00:10:30,945
         [all giggling]

271
00:10:30,981 --> 00:10:32,314
 <i> And then to the final stretch.</i>
      <i> They're neck and neck!</i>

272
00:10:32,349 --> 00:10:34,249
   <i> Now it's Piggy and Summer.</i>
   <i> Back to Gonzo and Animal.</i>

273
00:10:34,284 --> 00:10:36,084
 <i> No, back to Piggy and Summer!</i>

274
00:10:36,119 --> 00:10:37,952
    <i> This is a real nail-biter,</i>
              <i> folks.</i>

275
00:10:37,988 --> 00:10:39,954
       <i> It's anyone's race--</i>
     <i> and it's a photo finish!</i>

276
00:10:39,990 --> 00:10:43,124
  <i> Gonzo and Animal by a nose!</i>

277
00:10:43,160 --> 00:10:45,026
      [cheers and applause]
      both: Hooray! Hooray!

278
00:10:45,062 --> 00:10:46,294
- [laughs]

279
00:10:46,330 --> 00:10:48,963
              - Yes!
        - Good game, guys.

280
00:10:48,999 --> 00:10:51,132
                   And... Piggy?

281
00:10:51,168 --> 00:10:53,968
                 - That...was...

282
00:10:54,004 --> 00:10:56,004
                        awesome!

283
00:10:56,039 --> 00:10:57,272
            Good game, everyone!

284
00:10:57,307 --> 00:11:00,208
      [cheers and applause]

285
00:11:00,243 --> 00:11:02,210
       <i> [victorious music]</i>

286
00:11:02,245 --> 00:11:04,913
              <i> ♪ ♪</i>

287
00:11:04,948 --> 00:11:07,916
   [all cheering and laughing]

288
00:11:09,286 --> 00:11:11,186
- And now,
for winning two games

289
00:11:11,221 --> 00:11:13,254
at the first-ever
Muppets Sport-A-Thon,

290
00:11:13,290 --> 00:11:17,058
the gold medals made of
chocolate go to...

291
00:11:17,094 --> 00:11:19,027
Animal and Gonzo!

292
00:11:19,062 --> 00:11:21,229
                    - [laughing]

293
00:11:21,264 --> 00:11:23,031
                [chomps, laughs]

294
00:11:23,066 --> 00:11:25,233
                  Victory sweet.

295
00:11:25,268 --> 00:11:28,203
      - Good job, you guys.
            - Thanks.

296
00:11:28,238 --> 00:11:32,040
     Hey, Piggy, I know how much
      you wanted a gold medal...

297
00:11:32,075 --> 00:11:34,008
       so I want you to have it.

298
00:11:34,044 --> 00:11:36,945
- [stutters] A gold medal?
For moi?

299
00:11:36,980 --> 00:11:38,246
         [together] Aww.

300
00:11:38,281 --> 00:11:40,081
            - Hiyah!
            - [gasps]

301
00:11:40,117 --> 00:11:41,282
           [all gasp]

302
00:11:41,318 --> 00:11:43,251
- Piggy, what are you doing?

303
00:11:43,286 --> 00:11:46,020
   - I'm giving some gold medal
          to everybody,

304
00:11:46,056 --> 00:11:48,289
      because everyone wins
          when they try.

305
00:11:48,325 --> 00:11:51,292
           [all cheer]

306
00:11:51,328 --> 00:11:54,062
       - Maybe we should go over
         for some chocolate too.

307
00:11:54,097 --> 00:11:55,196
- No thanks.

308
00:11:55,232 --> 00:11:57,065
That last bit
was sweet enough for me.

309
00:11:57,100 --> 00:12:00,101
           [all laugh]

310
00:12:02,005 --> 00:12:05,907
            - "You Say 'Potato,'
           I Say 'Best Friend.'"

311
00:12:05,942 --> 00:12:07,041
                        [grunts]

312
00:12:07,077 --> 00:12:09,277
              Nice throw, buddy.

313
00:12:13,316 --> 00:12:16,284
- [gasps] Ooh, ooh!
Look at this one, Miss Nanny!

314
00:12:16,319 --> 00:12:20,021
- Wow, that's the shiniest
tomato I've ever seen.

315
00:12:20,056 --> 00:12:22,023
        - Until this one!

316
00:12:22,058 --> 00:12:25,226
- Super shiny, Summer,
but that's a bell pepper.

317
00:12:25,262 --> 00:12:28,096
                         - Bell?

318
00:12:28,131 --> 00:12:30,031
            I think it's broken.

319
00:12:30,066 --> 00:12:31,266
- I bet it was just
getting warmed up.

320
00:12:31,301 --> 00:12:33,134
Go on, try again.

321
00:12:33,170 --> 00:12:35,069
[imitating bell]
♪ Ding-a-ling-a-ling... ♪

322
00:12:35,105 --> 00:12:36,938
            - [gasps]
            - [laughs]

323
00:12:36,973 --> 00:12:39,007
                      [laughing]

324
00:12:39,042 --> 00:12:40,308
                            Huh?
                            Hmm.

325
00:12:40,343 --> 00:12:43,144
            What that?
        - I don't know...

326
00:12:43,180 --> 00:12:45,113
       but it's beautiful!

327
00:12:45,148 --> 00:12:48,116
    <i> [heavenly choral music]</i>

328
00:12:48,151 --> 00:12:50,151
- Well, would you look
at that, Gonzo?

329
00:12:50,187 --> 00:12:51,319
You found a potato.

330
00:12:51,354 --> 00:12:54,289
- Hello, Potato.
I'm Gonzo.

331
00:12:54,324 --> 00:12:56,291
   - Who put it in the ground,
           Miss Nanny?

332
00:12:56,326 --> 00:12:59,194
- Well, I guess I did
when I planted the seed.

333
00:12:59,229 --> 00:13:01,229
      Potatoes aren't like
      tomatoes or peppers.

334
00:13:01,264 --> 00:13:03,131
     They grow underground.

335
00:13:03,166 --> 00:13:06,134
- Ooh, sounds cozy.
[chuckles]

336
00:13:06,169 --> 00:13:07,936
- Thanks for your help,
everyone.

337
00:13:07,971 --> 00:13:09,170
I'm going to whip these veggies

338
00:13:09,206 --> 00:13:11,272
into a tasty salad
for snack time.

339
00:13:11,308 --> 00:13:13,141
      <i> [frantic string music]</i>
              - No!

340
00:13:13,176 --> 00:13:14,976
- Don't worry, Gonzo.

341
00:13:15,011 --> 00:13:17,111
This salad doesn't
include potatoes.

342
00:13:17,147 --> 00:13:18,913
           - [exhales]

343
00:13:18,949 --> 00:13:21,015
       I wouldn't want that
    to happen to you, Potato.

344
00:13:21,051 --> 00:13:23,084
- Well, what should we do now?

345
00:13:23,086 --> 00:13:24,285
             - Animal want play.

346
00:13:24,321 --> 00:13:26,955
- Okay.
Let's play rocket tag. do now?

347
00:13:26,990 --> 00:13:28,990
- Ooh!
What's rocket tag?

348
00:13:29,025 --> 00:13:30,191
        - It's kind of like tag.

349
00:13:30,227 --> 00:13:32,927
                - But we imagine
      we're wearing rocket shoes

350
00:13:32,963 --> 00:13:35,196
                   so we can fly
        all the way to the moon.

351
00:13:35,232 --> 00:13:38,266
    - Ooh, great idea, Kermie!
        And <i> I'll </i> be it.

352
00:13:38,301 --> 00:13:41,069
           [all cheer]
              - Hey.

353
00:13:41,104 --> 00:13:45,073
                  Where's Gonzo?
                          Gonzo?

354
00:13:45,108 --> 00:13:48,243
- Usually, vegetables are round
or long or pointy.

355
00:13:48,278 --> 00:13:51,112
I've never seen one
who looks like you.

356
00:13:51,147 --> 00:13:54,115
   I've got a funny shape too.
          [nose springs]

357
00:13:54,150 --> 00:13:56,251
But that's what
makes us special.

358
00:13:56,286 --> 00:13:58,152
We have a lot in common, huh?

359
00:13:58,188 --> 00:13:59,988
[gasps]
You know what?

360
00:14:00,023 --> 00:14:02,891
           I think that makes us
                           BFFs.

361
00:14:02,926 --> 00:14:04,025
       You know what that means?

362
00:14:04,060 --> 00:14:06,895
                        It means
         "best friends forever."

363
00:14:06,930 --> 00:14:08,129
                            BFF!

364
00:14:08,164 --> 00:14:10,231
                   How about it?

365
00:14:10,267 --> 00:14:12,233
             Oopsie.
       babies: There he is!

366
00:14:12,269 --> 00:14:15,103
- Um, Gonzo, why are you
playing with a potato?

367
00:14:15,138 --> 00:14:17,906
                  - Because he's
             my new best friend?

368
00:14:17,941 --> 00:14:19,207
- But it's a potato.

369
00:14:19,242 --> 00:14:21,943
             - Yeah!
      Potato, meet everyone.

370
00:14:21,978 --> 00:14:24,112
     Everyone, meet Potato.

371
00:14:24,147 --> 00:14:26,247
       [together] Uh...hi.
              - Hey.

372
00:14:26,283 --> 00:14:28,917
- [cackles]
French fry!

373
00:14:28,952 --> 00:14:31,920
- No, Animal!
I said "meet Potato,"

374
00:14:31,955 --> 00:14:34,055
        not "eat Potato"!
              - Oh.

375
00:14:34,090 --> 00:14:35,290
                             Hi.

376
00:14:35,325 --> 00:14:37,959
- Gonzo, do you wanna
play rocket tag with us?

377
00:14:37,994 --> 00:14:39,260
          - Can Potato play too?

378
00:14:39,296 --> 00:14:42,063
- Ooh, I've never played
with a vegetable before.

379
00:14:42,098 --> 00:14:44,933
              - Why don't we let
                   Potato be it?

380
00:14:44,968 --> 00:14:47,302
- [stuttering] But--
but it is a potato!

381
00:14:47,337 --> 00:14:49,270
      And it's my turn to be it.

382
00:14:49,306 --> 00:14:52,273
- Aw, come on, Piggy.
We can give Potato a chance.

383
00:14:52,309 --> 00:14:56,177
        - Well...I guess I could
            let it take my turn.

384
00:14:56,212 --> 00:14:58,279
        - Thanks, Piggy.
        He'll love that.

385
00:14:58,315 --> 00:15:00,181
        All right, Potato!
            You ready?

386
00:15:00,216 --> 00:15:02,250
         Tag, you're it!
     <i> [heavenly choral music]</i>

387
00:15:02,285 --> 00:15:05,887
        all: Rocket tag!

388
00:15:05,922 --> 00:15:08,022
         [all cheering]

389
00:15:08,058 --> 00:15:10,158
    - [laughs] Can't catch me!
             - Or me!

390
00:15:10,193 --> 00:15:12,160
           [all cheer]

391
00:15:12,195 --> 00:15:14,162
        - [laughs] Whoa!

392
00:15:14,197 --> 00:15:16,164
- [giggling]

393
00:15:16,199 --> 00:15:17,999
Can't catch me, Potato!

394
00:15:18,034 --> 00:15:19,133
       - Can't catch me, Potato!

395
00:15:19,169 --> 00:15:21,202
                      [laughing]

396
00:15:21,237 --> 00:15:23,071
- [laughs]

397
00:15:23,106 --> 00:15:24,939
[chomping]

398
00:15:24,975 --> 00:15:27,141
        - [laughing] Whoa!
  I hope Potato doesn't tag me.

399
00:15:27,177 --> 00:15:29,210
                   Whoo-hoo-hoo!

400
00:15:31,181 --> 00:15:33,281
      What's wrong, Potato?
           - Ooh, ooh!

401
00:15:33,316 --> 00:15:36,918
    [laughs] You're not gonna
       catch <i> me, </i> Potato!

402
00:15:36,953 --> 00:15:39,187
             [gasps]
       Well, I guess I win.

403
00:15:39,222 --> 00:15:40,922
             I win!

404
00:15:40,957 --> 00:15:43,124
- Why isn't Potato chasing us?

405
00:15:43,159 --> 00:15:45,226
- Uh, he's probably
just nervous.

406
00:15:45,261 --> 00:15:47,228
Being it is a lot of pressure.

407
00:15:47,263 --> 00:15:50,131
                   - I told you,
             it's just a potato.

408
00:15:50,166 --> 00:15:52,233
        It can't play tag!
         - You're right.

409
00:15:52,268 --> 00:15:54,235
So let's try a different game.

410
00:15:54,270 --> 00:15:55,970
- Oh, oh!
I know!

411
00:15:56,006 --> 00:15:57,939
Let's have a bike race.

412
00:15:57,974 --> 00:16:01,909
   - Way ahead of you, Summer.
        [imitates engine]

413
00:16:01,945 --> 00:16:04,912
        [engines revving]

414
00:16:05,181 --> 00:16:07,882
          - Don't worry, Potato.
              Racing is a blast.

415
00:16:07,917 --> 00:16:09,017
                  Just go faster
             than everyone else,

416
00:16:09,052 --> 00:16:11,119
                    and you win.
                    - Good luck!

417
00:16:11,154 --> 00:16:14,122
The only winner here today
will be moi.

418
00:16:14,157 --> 00:16:16,124
                - Ready...set...

419
00:16:16,159 --> 00:16:17,925
                 Go-go-go-go-go!

420
00:16:17,961 --> 00:16:19,927
         [tires squeal]

421
00:16:19,963 --> 00:16:21,262
        [crowd cheering]

422
00:16:21,297 --> 00:16:23,965
         [all cheering]

423
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:25,233
        - Yay! Go, racers!
         - Yay, yay, yay!

424
00:16:25,268 --> 00:16:27,969
          <i> [rock music]</i>

425
00:16:28,004 --> 00:16:30,038
- Too slow!

426
00:16:30,073 --> 00:16:32,040
              <i> ♪ ♪</i>

427
00:16:32,075 --> 00:16:34,042
      <i> [crickets chirping]</i>

428
00:16:34,077 --> 00:16:35,276
           - Whoo-hoo!
             - Whee!

429
00:16:35,311 --> 00:16:37,045
             - Whoa!

430
00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:43,251
              <i> ♪ ♪</i>

431
00:16:43,286 --> 00:16:46,154
         - [gasps] Piggy!
      Watch out for Potato!

432
00:16:46,189 --> 00:16:48,189
            [all gasp]
            - Potato!

433
00:16:48,224 --> 00:16:52,060
       Get out of the way!

434
00:16:52,095 --> 00:16:55,063
            [screams]

435
00:16:55,098 --> 00:16:56,264
           [both gasp]

436
00:16:56,299 --> 00:17:01,235
             - Whoa!
           - [screams]

437
00:17:03,940 --> 00:17:05,239
                     - [huffing]

438
00:17:05,275 --> 00:17:08,042
    Ugh! I was going to win!

439
00:17:08,078 --> 00:17:10,011
              Humph.
    That potato got in my way.

440
00:17:10,046 --> 00:17:12,246
- Sorry, Piggy.
He didn't mean to.

441
00:17:12,282 --> 00:17:14,949
     - I guess he isn't good
        at racing, either.

442
00:17:14,984 --> 00:17:16,217
                      - Uh, hey.
               Instead of games,

443
00:17:16,252 --> 00:17:18,886
              maybe Potato wants
       to put on a play with us.

444
00:17:18,922 --> 00:17:20,121
                  - Yes, a play.

445
00:17:20,156 --> 00:17:24,058
And moi will be
the director extraordinaire.

446
00:17:24,094 --> 00:17:27,028
             [singsong] You have
        one more chance, Potato!

447
00:17:27,063 --> 00:17:30,098
                 [clears throat]
               Places, everyone!

448
00:17:30,133 --> 00:17:32,100
    - You're gonna be a star!

449
00:17:32,135 --> 00:17:35,103
  <i> [building orchestral music]</i>

450
00:17:35,138 --> 00:17:37,205
              <i> ♪ ♪</i>

451
00:17:37,240 --> 00:17:40,074
- Okay, everyone.
Let's take it from the top.

452
00:17:40,110 --> 00:17:41,142
      [cheers and applause]
              - Yay!

453
00:17:41,177 --> 00:17:44,178
                     - Whoo-hoo!

454
00:17:44,214 --> 00:17:47,915
- To be green
or not to be green?

455
00:17:47,951 --> 00:17:51,119
That is the question.

456
00:17:51,154 --> 00:17:53,054
      [cheers and applause]
        - Encore, encore!

457
00:17:53,089 --> 00:17:55,056
- Bravissimo!

458
00:17:55,091 --> 00:17:58,092
       - Oh, bravo, Kermie!
         [giggles] Bravo!

459
00:17:58,128 --> 00:18:01,863
            And next,
   "A Midsummer Night's Dance."

460
00:18:01,898 --> 00:18:04,866
    <i> [sweeping ballet music]</i>

461
00:18:04,901 --> 00:18:11,873
              <i> ♪ ♪</i>

462
00:18:13,009 --> 00:18:15,977
      [cheers and applause]

463
00:18:16,012 --> 00:18:18,012
  <i> - Très magnifique, </i> Summer.

464
00:18:18,047 --> 00:18:20,882
            - [laughs excitedly]
       Now Potato's gonna finish

465
00:18:20,917 --> 00:18:22,917
    with his big musical number!

466
00:18:22,952 --> 00:18:24,252
           [drum roll]

467
00:18:24,287 --> 00:18:26,087
               ♪ ♪

468
00:18:26,122 --> 00:18:27,922
        [cymbal crashes]

469
00:18:28,224 --> 00:18:31,192
       [sad trombone tune]

470
00:18:33,129 --> 00:18:35,897
           - That's it!
      The potato's gotta go.

471
00:18:35,932 --> 00:18:38,032
                    - [stammers]
   Potato just forgot his lines.

472
00:18:38,067 --> 00:18:39,967
   It could happen to any of us.

473
00:18:40,003 --> 00:18:41,068
- I don't know.

474
00:18:41,104 --> 00:18:43,905
I thought Potato
was very "a-peel-ing."

475
00:18:43,940 --> 00:18:46,908
Peel?
A potato? Eh?

476
00:18:46,943 --> 00:18:48,943
What?
Not the time?

477
00:18:48,978 --> 00:18:52,079
  That tater tot ruined my play.
            - Piggy...

478
00:18:52,115 --> 00:18:54,182
- Ugh, I can't
take it anymore, Kermie!

479
00:18:54,217 --> 00:18:57,285
The potato is ruining
all our fun!

480
00:18:57,320 --> 00:18:59,954
         - [gasps] I know
    we can all play together.

481
00:18:59,989 --> 00:19:02,089
      We just haven't found
   the right game for him yet.

482
00:19:02,125 --> 00:19:04,225
- But Gonzo,
what <i> is </i> the right game?

483
00:19:04,260 --> 00:19:06,093
- Potato can't run.

484
00:19:06,129 --> 00:19:07,995
                      - No ride.

485
00:19:08,031 --> 00:19:09,130
                      - Or sing.

486
00:19:09,165 --> 00:19:10,965
- It can't do anything!

487
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:12,166
I'm not playing
with that potato

488
00:19:12,202 --> 00:19:14,936
for another minute.

489
00:19:14,971 --> 00:19:16,871
- Oh, Gonzo.
Maybe you can just

490
00:19:16,906 --> 00:19:18,139
put Potato back in the garden.

491
00:19:18,174 --> 00:19:19,907
     - You want me to ignore him

492
00:19:19,943 --> 00:19:21,909
                    just because
          he can't play like us?

493
00:19:21,945 --> 00:19:23,211
                    So Potato is
             a little different.

494
00:19:23,246 --> 00:19:25,947
               That doesn't mean
     we shouldn't be his friend.

495
00:19:25,982 --> 00:19:28,015
                   Can't you see
              how special he is?

496
00:19:28,051 --> 00:19:29,116
    <i> [heavenly choral music]</i>

497
00:19:29,152 --> 00:19:31,085
           - Uh...um...
           - I guess..

498
00:19:31,154 --> 00:19:32,987
                         - Fine.

499
00:19:33,022 --> 00:19:34,889
         Maybe you can just stop
      being friends with someone

500
00:19:34,924 --> 00:19:37,058
   because they're not like you,
                    but I can't.

501
00:19:37,093 --> 00:19:39,060
         If you can't find a way
              to include Potato,

502
00:19:39,095 --> 00:19:40,228
    we'll just go play alone.

503
00:19:40,263 --> 00:19:42,096
          <i> [sad music]</i>

504
00:19:42,131 --> 00:19:45,066
- Uh, does anyone wanna hear
another potato joke?

505
00:19:45,101 --> 00:19:47,902
       - Too soon, Fozzie.

506
00:19:47,937 --> 00:19:49,070
      - It's okay, Potato.

507
00:19:49,105 --> 00:19:51,939
        So you can't run
        or sing or ride.

508
00:19:51,975 --> 00:19:57,245
          I don't mind.
       I'm still your BFF,

509
00:19:57,280 --> 00:19:59,247
          and that means
    <i> [upbeat twanging music]</i>

510
00:19:59,282 --> 00:20:02,183
              <i> ♪ ♪</i>

511
00:20:02,218 --> 00:20:04,252
♪ Me and my Potato ♪

512
00:20:04,287 --> 00:20:07,054
♪ Walking through the yard ♪

513
00:20:07,090 --> 00:20:11,092
     ♪ No one understands you
           like I do ♪

514
00:20:11,127 --> 00:20:13,094
                           Sure,
      you're a little different.

515
00:20:13,129 --> 00:20:16,063
        ♪ But I don't get
        why it's so hard ♪

516
00:20:16,099 --> 00:20:21,002
      ♪ For everyone to see
     what's great about you ♪

517
00:20:21,037 --> 00:20:25,273
♪ Best friends come
in every shape and size ♪

518
00:20:25,308 --> 00:20:27,241
♪ You don't need arms or legs ♪

519
00:20:27,277 --> 00:20:31,178
♪ Or ears or nose
or mouth or eyes ♪

520
00:20:31,214 --> 00:20:33,281
       ♪ To be my Potato ♪

521
00:20:33,316 --> 00:20:36,017
  ♪ And my best friend, yeah ♪

522
00:20:36,052 --> 00:20:40,121
     ♪ It's me and my Potato
          till the end ♪

523
00:20:40,156 --> 00:20:43,124
- Humph! The potato would've
made a mess of this game.

524
00:20:43,159 --> 00:20:45,226
Good thing we don't have to
play with him anymore.

525
00:20:45,261 --> 00:20:47,194
        - Yeah... [grunts]
       But we also don't...

526
00:20:47,230 --> 00:20:49,163
       [grunts] Get to play
       with Gonzo anymore.

527
00:20:49,198 --> 00:20:51,299
        [grunts, warbles]

528
00:20:51,334 --> 00:20:54,168
- Oh, I miss Gonzo.

529
00:20:54,203 --> 00:20:56,971
He's the best
double-Dutcher I know.

530
00:20:57,006 --> 00:20:59,106
- Well, he shouldn't have
made us play with a potato.

531
00:20:59,142 --> 00:21:00,908
He ruined all our games.

532
00:21:00,944 --> 00:21:03,978
   - Remember when I moved here
       from the South Pole?

533
00:21:04,013 --> 00:21:07,181
         I was so nervous
    about you guys liking me.

534
00:21:07,216 --> 00:21:10,084
- Animal like summer! [laughs]

535
00:21:10,119 --> 00:21:12,253
           - We all do.
             - Sure,

536
00:21:12,288 --> 00:21:15,056
            but it took me time
            to learn your games.

537
00:21:15,091 --> 00:21:17,058
              Now I can do this!

538
00:21:17,093 --> 00:21:19,093
             Hoo-hah!
        Hoo-hah! [laughs]

539
00:21:19,128 --> 00:21:21,128
                   - Impressive.

540
00:21:21,164 --> 00:21:22,997
        - But when I didn't know
                    how to play,

541
00:21:23,032 --> 00:21:26,133
             you guys taught me.
          You never left me out.

542
00:21:26,169 --> 00:21:28,936
             - Because you don't
              leave friends out.

543
00:21:28,972 --> 00:21:31,005
- Bad friends.

544
00:21:31,040 --> 00:21:32,940
  - Potato doesn't fit in yet,

545
00:21:32,976 --> 00:21:35,109
          but I'm going
     to welcome him anyway--

546
00:21:35,144 --> 00:21:38,112
  the way you guys welcome me!

547
00:21:38,147 --> 00:21:41,115
- Um, I suppose it was
a teensy bit mean

548
00:21:41,150 --> 00:21:42,984
      to leave Potato out.

549
00:21:43,019 --> 00:21:44,051
[stammers] Come on!

550
00:21:44,087 --> 00:21:45,987
Let's go ask
our friends to play.

551
00:21:46,022 --> 00:21:48,956
         [all cheering]

552
00:21:48,992 --> 00:21:50,257
         - Gonzo! Gonzo!

553
00:21:50,293 --> 00:21:52,326
          - Are you here to make
          Potato feel bad again?

554
00:21:52,362 --> 00:21:54,128
- No.

555
00:21:54,163 --> 00:21:55,963
          We didn't have any fun
               playing with you.

556
00:21:55,999 --> 00:21:57,231
- We came over to say

557
00:21:57,266 --> 00:22:00,267
that any friend of yours
is a friend of ours too.

558
00:22:00,303 --> 00:22:05,139
        - We didn't mean to make
        Potato or you feel bad.

559
00:22:05,174 --> 00:22:07,141
                We'll try harder
                to include it--

560
00:22:07,176 --> 00:22:09,010
         [stammers] I mean, him.

561
00:22:09,045 --> 00:22:11,045
- Thanks, Piggy.
See, Potato?

562
00:22:11,080 --> 00:22:13,080
I told you they were
good friends.

563
00:22:13,116 --> 00:22:15,149
- Animal love Potato!

564
00:22:15,184 --> 00:22:18,252
           - [warbling]
             Whoa-oa!

565
00:22:18,287 --> 00:22:21,022
- So you'll forgive us, Gonzo?

566
00:22:21,057 --> 00:22:23,290
           - Of course.
      What are friends for?

567
00:22:23,326 --> 00:22:25,159
                  - Don't worry.

568
00:22:25,194 --> 00:22:27,128
       I know we can find a game
          that you can play too.

569
00:22:27,163 --> 00:22:30,231
- [gasps] Oh! I know
the perfect game for everyone!

570
00:22:30,266 --> 00:22:33,034
Best friend hot potato!

571
00:22:33,069 --> 00:22:35,102
Remember,
whoever has the potato

572
00:22:35,138 --> 00:22:38,172
when the music stops
wins.

573
00:22:38,207 --> 00:22:39,173
          [music stops]

574
00:22:39,208 --> 00:22:41,042
                      - [laughs]

575
00:22:41,077 --> 00:22:43,110
- [laughs] I win!

576
00:22:43,146 --> 00:22:45,146
You really are fun, Potato.

577
00:22:45,181 --> 00:22:49,116
      Best friend handshake.
            [grunting]

578
00:22:49,152 --> 00:22:50,985
          Sorry, Gonzo.

579
00:22:51,020 --> 00:22:53,120
       I forgot Potato was
       <i> your </i> best friend.

580
00:22:53,156 --> 00:22:56,090
           - No, Piggy.
   He's everyone's best friend.

581
00:22:56,125 --> 00:22:58,259
                      - Come on!
               Let's play again.

582
00:22:58,294 --> 00:23:00,061
  all: Best friend hot potato!

